  "body": "Context on #6041\r\n\r\nWe currently only accept `data` as the name of the payload field when during an eth_call (and presumably other transaction-related RPCs) https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/a90ea056f19915a4eca787fc066c080e1789c14c/ethereum/api/src/main/java/org/hyperledger/besu/ethereum/api/jsonrpc/internal/parameters/JsonCallParameter.java#L52-L53\r\n\r\nThe spec requires `input` as the name instead:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis/blob/057892b256c181232ca22499d1801b9637192698/src/schemas/transaction.yaml#L33\r\n\r\nWe will need to continue accepting `data` to avoid forcing a lot of tooling to update.\r\n\r\nWe should add support for `input` xor `data`",
